## Summary

I successfully analyzed the memory leak bug in the VS Code diff editor and proposed a fix:

### Bug Analysis

**Root Cause**: The `EditorGutter` class in `src/vs/editor/browser/widget/diffEditor/utils/editorGutter.ts` has a memory leak in its `dispose()` method. The class maintains a `Map` of gutter item views, but when the EditorGutter is disposed, these views are never cleaned up. This causes diff editor widgets and their associated resources to remain in memory even after the editors are closed.

### The Fix

Modify the `dispose()` method in `EditorGutter` to properly dispose all views before cleanup:

```typescript
override dispose(): void {
    super.dispose();

    // Dispose all remaining views to prevent memory leak
    for (const [_id, view] of this.views) {
        view.gutterItemView.dispose();
        view.domNode.remove();
    }
    this.views.clear();

    reset(this._domNode);
}
```

### Confidence: High

The analysis is strongly supported by:
1. Issue comments explicitly mentioning views in EditorGutter not being disposed
2. Heap snapshot evidence pointing to `gutterFeature` as the retainer
3. Clear code pattern showing proper disposal during render but not during final cleanup
4. Git history showing similar memory leak fixes in the same timeframe

The proposed fix document has been written to `/Users/penlv/Code/Work/sounds-gucci/data/analysis/286385/proposed-fix.md` with complete details about the bug, analysis process, and solution.

